      "raw_text": "A flax mill for the Inland Empire\nand a factory to manufacture lin\nseed oil are advocated by Mayor\nMoore. who in talking over the mat\nter this morning, stated that there\nwas q field here for a mill which\nhad an output of 100 barrels of oil\na day.\n\n\nThere is plenty of flax grown in\nthis vicinity, but the raw material\nis all shipped east and the Spokane\nand Inland Empire consumers pay\na difference of ABBOTT 90 cents a gal.\nIon as result of the freight rates\n1t is also argued that were the mill\nerected 1t would give an added i'm\npetus to flax raising In this section\nand would make IL one of the profit\nable crops of the farm."
